Greens/weeds harvested from the field might contain poisonous plants but usually, commercial feeds are safe only when all the requirements on storage and transportation/application are adhered to.
To know the cause of the problem, I would recommend that a post-mortem is done on the carcass (or sacrifice one that looks sick) to identify the pathological lesions and affected organs as this can tell the probable cause of death.
To avoid such losses that may arise due to management malpractices, ensure you use appropriate fresh greens/commercial feeds for rabbits, maintain hygiene in the rabbit’s enclosures, proper stocking rates and seek veterinary advice on disease control measures available in your country.
Dr Ngetich Wyckliff- Department of Veterinary Surgery, Theriogenology and Medicine, Egerton University.
****
Crops you can farm in Nyanza
As commercial viability of sugarcane wanes in Nyanza, I need to know what other crops can one successfully grow in the region?
Paul 
There are so many crops that can do well in Nyanza. Watermelons, sweet potatoes, tomatoes, sorghum, millet, mangoes, pawpaw, oranges, bananas and indigenous vegetables like cowpea, spider plant, terere and black nightshade all perform well.



