****
Buying heifers
I need heifers, please help.
Amos Oreno
Many dairy farms sell heifers and in-calf heifers but the most important point to consider is which part of the country are you going to rear the animals.
This is important because of environmental variations like temperature that affect the heifers. Another factor is the objective of setting up the farm, that is, are you interested in milk quality or quantity.
Market survey is equally important to help you choose production based on market demand. You did not specify where you are but we can point you to selected dairy farms where you can get heifers.
Dairy management hands-on skills are also extremely important as you venture into the business.
Dennis Kigiri, Department of Animal Sciences, Egerton University.
****
Lime application
At what time does one apply lime. Please explain. 
Peterson
Lime is a soil amendment that helps to increase the pH, thereby reducing its acidity. First, you need to test your soil to find out the acidity level before applying the lime.
Testing the soil is also mandatory, since it will help your expert in calculating the lime requirement of your farm, since different farm soils require different amounts of lime to bring the pH to the desired level.



